cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is about improving the training of generative adversarial networks (GANs) using a new method called Gang of GANs (GoGAN). The paper focuses on visual datasets and proposes a new way of measuring GAN quality based on image completion tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper proposes a new training paradigm involving multiple GANs, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper includes theoretical analysis and proposes a new loss function, cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible sub-category as well.
